================================================================================
COMPREHENSIVE VERSION MISMATCH AUDITOR & FIXER
================================================================================

MISSION: Scan entire project for ALL version mismatches, conflicts, and 
incompatibilities. Auto-resolve to stable, compatible LTS versions.

================================================================================
SCAN PHASE 1: DETECT ALL VERSIONS
================================================================================

ACTION: Scan Node.js ecosystem
SCAN:
  - package.json (all dependencies, devDependencies, optionalDependencies)
  - package-lock.json (locked versions)
  - .npmrc (npm registry settings)
  - .nvmrc (Node version)

ACTION: Scan Python ecosystem
SCAN:
  - requirements.txt (pinned versions)
  - requirements-dev.txt (dev dependencies)
  - setup.py (if present)
  - pyproject.toml (if present)
  - Pipfile (if present)
  - poetry.lock (if present)
  - runtime.txt (Python version for Heroku/Render)

ACTION: Scan Docker (if present)
SCAN:
  - Dockerfile (base images, versions)
  - docker-compose.yml (service versions)
  - .dockerignore

ACTION: Scan API & External Services
SCAN:
  - Requirements for Gemini SDK (google-generativeai)
  - Requirements for Pinecone (pinecone-client)
  - Requirements for Neon driver (psycopg2, asyncpg)
  - Requirements for FastAPI (fastapi, uvicorn)
  - Requirements for Next.js (check package.json)

ACTION: Scan Database & ORM versions
SCAN:
  - SQLAlchemy version compatibility
  - PostgreSQL driver compatibility
  - Migration tool versions (Alembic, etc)

ACTION: Scan Build Tools
SCAN:
  - TypeScript (typescript version in package.json)
  - tsconfig.json (target, lib versions)
  - Webpack (if present)
  - Tailwind (tailwind.config.js/ts)
  - ESLint (if present)

================================================================================
ANALYSIS PHASE 2: IDENTIFY CONFLICTS
================================================================================

FOR EACH DEPENDENCY:
  1. Check current version
  2. Check minimum required version
  3. Check known incompatibilities:
     - Peer dependency conflicts
     - Breaking changes between versions
     - Security vulnerabilities (check npm audit, pip audit)
     - Incompatible transitive dependencies

SPECIFIC CHECKS:

Node.js Conflicts:
  - Next.js 14 requires Node.js 18.17+
  - React 18 with Next.js 14
  - Shadcn/ui with Tailwind version match
  - Framer-motion compatibility
  - Lucide-react version

Python Conflicts:
  - SQLAlchemy 2.0+ requires Python 3.7+
  - FastAPI requires Python 3.7+
  - psycopg2 with PostgreSQL version
  - Pinecone SDK compatibility
  - google-generativeai compatibility
  - scikit-learn with numpy version match
  - pandas with numpy compatibility
  - lightgbm with numpy/scipy versions

API Conflicts:
  - Gemini API version constraints
  - Pinecone API client vs index version
  - Neon PostgreSQL driver version

================================================================================
RESOLUTION PHASE 3: FIX CONFLICTS
================================================================================

STRATEGY 1: USE STABLE LTS VERSIONS

Recommended versions:
  Node.js: 20.x LTS (latest stable)
  Python: 3.11.x LTS (latest stable)
  Next.js: 14.x
  React: 18.x
  TypeScript: 5.3+
  Tailwind: 3.3+

STRATEGY 2: RESOLVE PEER DEPENDENCIES

For each conflict:
  1. Identify which version is blocking others
  2. Find lowest compatible version that satisfies all constraints
  3. Document rationale in RESOLUTION_NOTES.md

STRATEGY 3: UPDATE LOCK FILES

Commands to execute:
  npm ci --package-lock-only  (regenerate npm lock file)
  pip freeze > requirements-frozen.txt  (capture exact versions)
  npm audit fix  (fix security issues)
  pip audit  (check Python security)

STRATEGY 4: VALIDATE COMPATIBILITY

For each major dependency group:
  1. Run package.json/requirements.txt linter
  2. Check for circular dependencies
  3. Verify transitive dependency resolution
  4. Test imports (basic smoke test)

================================================================================
EXECUTION: GENERATE FIXES
================================================================================

